==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prelibation
<hw>Pre`li*ba"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praelibatio</ets>, fr. <ets>praelibare</ets> to taste beforehand:
cf. F. <ets>prelibation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A tasting
beforehand, or by anticipation; a foretaste; <as>as, a
<ex>prelibation</ex> of heavenly bliss</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A pouring out, or libation, before
tasting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preliminarily</ent>⟦br⟧
